#use wml::debian::template title="Submit Mirror Information"

<p>If you would like to submit information about a mirror of Debian
(FTP archive, web), you can do so using this form. There is
an example at the bottom of the page in case you are unsure how
to proceed. If you need to submit changes, simply make
a new (complete) submission and add a comment stating it is an update.

<p><strong>Note:</strong> not all information provided will be
displayed in the mirror list (such as the mirror maintainer address).

<form method=post action="http://cgi.debian.org/cgi-bin/submit_mirror.pl">

<define-tag tablerow>
	<tr><td>%0: <td><input type="text" name="%1" size="%2">
</define-tag>

Site: <input type="text" name="site" size="30"><br>
Aliases: (comma separated list) <input type="text" name="aliases" size="60"><br>

<H2>Types of mirrors and methods of accessing them</H2>

<p>Enter the paths to the Debian mirror on your site in the fields below.
Leave non-relevant fields blank.

<table>
<tablerow "Packages archive, over HTTP"   archive-http   30>
<tablerow "Packages archive, over FTP"    archive-ftp    30>
<tablerow "Packages archive, over rsync"  archive-rsync  30>
<tablerow "Packages archive, over NFS"    archive-nfs    30>
<tablerow "Non-US packages, over HTTP"    nonus-http     30>
<tablerow "Non-US packages, over FTP"     nonus-ftp      30>
<tablerow "Non-US packages, over rsync"   nonus-rsync    30>
<tablerow "Non-US packages, over NFS"     nonus-nfs      30>
<tablerow "CD images, over HTTP"          cdimage-http   30>
<tablerow "CD images, over FTP"           cdimage-ftp    30>
<tablerow "CD images, over rsync"         cdimage-rsync  30>
<tablerow "CD images, over NFS"           cdimage-nfs    30>
<tablerow "Old Debian releases, over HTTP"  old-http     30>
<tablerow "Old Debian releases, over FTP"   old-ftp      30>
<tablerow "Old Debian releases, over rsync" old-rsync    30>
<tablerow "Old Debian releases, over NFS"   old-nfs      30>
<tablerow "Debian web pages, over HTTP"   www-http       30>
<tablerow "Debian web pages, over FTP"    www-ftp        30>
<tablerow "Debian web pages, over rsync"  www-rsync      30>
<tablerow "Debian web pages, over NFS"    www-nfs        30>
</table>

<H2>Information about the mirror site</H2>

<p>Please fill in all of the following (we will not disclose the name and
e-mail to anyone). The country and mirror origin are important since we use
that to organize the entries.

<table>
<tablerow "Mirrors from"                    mirrors_from  30>
<tablerow "Name of site maintainer"         maint_name    30>
<tablerow "Email of site maintainer"        maint_email   30>
# <tablerow "Country of site"                 country       30>
#	<tr><td>Country of site: <td><input type="text" name="country" size="30">
<tr><td>Country of site:  <td><select name="country">
#include "$(ENGLISHDIR)/mirror/countries.data"
<: country_list() :>
</select>
<tablerow "Location of site (optional)"     location      30>
<tablerow "Name of site sponsor (optional)" sponsor_name  30>
<tablerow "URL of site sponsor (optional)"  sponsor_url   30>
</table>

<table border=0><tr>
<td valign="top">Comment:</td>
<td><textarea name="comment" cols=40 rows=7 maxlength=256 wrap=virtual></textarea></td>
</tr></table>

<p>Note: if there is more than one sponsor, add the others in the comment.
You may also want to note if a mirror is partial, how often does it get
updated, and how fast the site is (its maximum bandwidth).
<br>

<input type="submit" value="Submit"> <input type="reset" value="Clear form">
</form>

<p>Your site will appear on the list within a week. We might email you in
case of any problems with the submitted entry.


<H2>Examples</H2>

<p>The following submission would be for http://ftp.debian.org/debian/.
<br>
Note that the path should point at the root of the Debian archive mirror.

<blockquote>
Site: <code>ftp.debian.org</code><br>
Aliases: <code>saens.debian.org</code><br>
Packages archive, over HTTP: <code>/debian/</code>
</blockquote>

<p>This is for ftp://ftp.debian.org/debian/:
     
<blockquote>
Packages archive, over FTP: <code>/debian/</code>
</blockquote>

<p>This is the directory used for rsync access (note that on many sites,
this may not be anonymous accessible), ftp.debian.org::debian/:

<blockquote>
Packages archive, over rsync: <code>debian/</code>
</blockquote>

<p>Now for the maintainer information:

<blockquote>
Name of site maintainer: <code>Debian FTP admins</code><br>
Email of site maintainer: <code>&lt;abc@address.goes.here&gt;</code>
</blockquote>

<p>(Once again, the maintainer address will not be shown on the public lists,
please enter a correct address.) The other information would be:

<blockquote>
Country: <code>US United States</code><br>
Comment: <code>Any notes you feel would help others</code>
</blockquote>

<p>Next example:

<p>This means the Debian web pages can be accessed at
http://www.uk.debian.org/:

<blockquote>
Site: <code>www.uk.debian.org</code><br>
Aliases: <code>open.hands.com</code><br>
Debian web pages, over HTTP: <code>/</code>
</blockquote>

<p>This is the directory used for rsync access to the web pages:
(BTW, this is <strong>not</strong> anonymous accessible.)

<blockquote>
Debian web pages, over rsync: <code>debian-web/</code><br>
</blockquote>

<p>Finally, the maintainer information:

<blockquote>
Name of site maintainer: <code>Philip Hands</code><br>
Email of site maintainer: <code>&lt;abc@address.goes.here&gt;</code><br>
Country: <code>GB Great Britain</code>
</blockquote>

<p>Next example would describe the mirror at ftp.uk.debian.org:

<blockquote>
Site: <code>ftp.uk.debian.org</code><br>
Aliases: <code>open.hands.com</code><br>
Packages archive, over HTTP: <code>/debian/</code><br>
Packages archive, over FTP: <code>/debian/</code><br>
Packages archive, over rsync: <code>debian/</code><br>
Name of site maintainer: <code>Philip Hands</code><br>
Email of site maintainer: <code>&lt;abc@address.goes.here&gt;</code><br>
Country: <code>GB Great Britain</code>
</blockquote>

<P>The entry for 'Site:' should contain the name under which you wish the mirror
to be listed, with other names listed under Aliases. This is probably the
reverse of the DNS entries, as in the example above for ftp.uk.debian.org.
Additionally, web and archive mirrors should get separate listings, as in the
second example above.

<p>If you maintain copies of old versions of Debian, your entry would look
something like this:

<blockquote>
Site: <code>archive.debian.org</code><br>
Old Debian releases, over HTTP: <code>/debian-archive/</code><br>
Old Debian releases, over FTP: <code>/debian-archive/</code><br>
Old Debian releases, over rsync: <code>debian-archive/</code><br>
Name of site maintainer: <code>Debian FTP admins</code><br>
Email of site maintainer: <code>&lt;abc@address.goes.here&gt;</code><br>
Country: <code>US United States</code><br>
</blockquote>
